        "text": "In general, use numerals to express numbers 10 and above, and use words to express numbers zero through nine.\n\nHowever, there are exceptions to this general guideline for number usage. There are cases in which you should always use numerals to express numbers, even numbers zero through nine, and likewise, there are cases in which you should always use words to express numbers, even numbers 10 and above."
